                                        1564
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": "contrast medium, there will be parts, where almost no motion occurs over time. In this case, an adaptive temporal scaling is advantageous, which performs iteratively a further decomposition, if subsequent frames are similar enough. If there are no changes over several frames, they shall be represented by only one LP frame. For significant changes among subsequent frames, for example when the contrast medium gets visible, these changes shall be represented in the LP subband with finer temporal resolution."
